parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the emergency trunk release system can lead to entrapment, potentially causing serious injury or death.
symptoms: The emergency trunk release system fails to operate
whether the electrical power is on
off
or in accessory mode.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: An electrical system fire can cause significant damage to the vehicle, potentially leading to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Smoke emanates from the hood vent
followed by a fire in the passenger footwell and engine area
even after the vehicle has been turned off.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the instrument cluster LED display can lead to driver error, as vital information such as gear selection, temperature, and time is not visible, potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: The instrument cluster LED display is faulty
making it difficult or impossible to see gear selection
temperature
and time.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Sudden engine stalling can cause accidents, especially when the vehicle is in motion, as the driver may lose control of the vehicle.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly shuts down while in motion
making it difficult or impossible to restart or shift into neutral.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can lead to serious injury or even fatalities in the event of a crash, as the airbags may not deploy as intended, leaving occupants vulnerable to harm.
symptoms: The SRS warning light remains on
airbags fail to deploy in a crash
airbags deploy unexpectedly
or the airbag system malfunctions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the emissions system can cause the vehicle to fail emissions tests, resulting in fines and penalties, and potentially leading to environmental harm.
symptoms: The vehicle fails to pass emissions tests
the "Check Engine" light is illuminated
the vehicle's onboard diagnostic system (OBD) displays a specific trouble code (e.g. P-700)
the vehicle's performance is affected
the vehicle's fuel efficiency is decreased.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended acceleration of the vehicle can cause loss of control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly and uncontrollably
despite the driver's attempts to apply the brakes
crossing multiple lanes of traffic
and potentially colliding with other vehicles or objects.
